\h LIGHT \d

\uUSAGE\n
!light lightSource \s[\dfireSource\s]\d

\uDESCRIPTION\n
Ignite a light source (a torch or oil lamp) using a) a tinderbox, or b) a lit torch or oil lamp.
You may omit the second argument, in which case the first tinderbox in your inventory will be used.

To light the torch in your readied equipment:
\qlight \le#l\qtorch\d4`
...or just...
\qlight torch\d4`

To light the torch in your inventory:
\qlight \li#l\qtorch\d4`

Note that a lit torch or lamp in your inventory will not illuminate the room: you must ready the light source or drop it on the ground.

\uEXAMPLES\n
\qlight torch\d to light your torch (in your readied equipment) using your tinderbox (in your inventory).4`
\qlight \p2#i\qtorch\d to light your second torch.4`
\qlight torch \p2#i\qtinderbox\d to light your torch using your second tinderbox.4`
\qlight \li#l\p2#i\qtorch\d to light your second torch (in your inventory).4`

\uSEE ALSO\n
drop, extinguish, prefixes, ready, refuel
